doc.previous: As of July 2010 a total of 65 F27s were in commercial service with almost 30 different airlines.[2] By July 2013 only 25 Friendships remained in service, operated by 13 different airlines; most were F27-500s, with two -400s and a solitary -600 series aircraft in service. Italian cargo airline MiniLiner operated six F27s and Air Panama had four in its fleet.[3] The United States Army Parachute Team has used a C-31A Troopship for its skydiving exhibitions since 1985.[4]
